---
title: "Sequence Diagram: /create-mermaid Skill"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant FS as File System

    User->>Claude: /create-mermaid [type] [name] [description]

    alt No type provided
        Claude->>Claude: Infer best diagram type<br/>from description
    end

    note over Claude,FS: Read rules
    Claude->>FS: Read mermaid-style.md
    FS-->>Claude: Style constraints
    Claude->>FS: Read how-to-create-mermaid.md
    FS-->>Claude: Full guide + examples

    note over Claude,FS: Analyze subject
    alt User describes a flow or process
        Claude->>Claude: Choose sequence or flow
    else User describes states or lifecycle
        Claude->>Claude: Choose state
    else User describes structure
        Claude->>Claude: Choose class or er
    end

    opt User references code
        Claude->>FS: Read relevant source files
        FS-->>Claude: Real architecture
    end

    opt User references a skill or agent
        Claude->>FS: Read SKILL.md / agent .md
        FS-->>Claude: Workflow to diagram
    end

    note over Claude,FS: Generate .mmd file
    Claude->>Claude: Build diagram:<br/>neutral theme, no hardcoded colors,<br/>participants declared first,<br/>max 10 participants
    alt Sequence diagram for a skill
        Claude->>FS: Write sequences/name.mmd
    else Other diagram
        Claude->>FS: Write docs/name.mmd
    end
    FS-->>Claude: OK

    note over Claude,FS: Verify
    Claude->>FS: Read generated file
    FS-->>Claude: Content

    Claude->>Claude: Check: neutral theme present,<br/>no rect rgb, no inline styles,<br/>no hardcoded colors

    Claude->>User: [CREATED] path/name.mmd<br/>[THEME] neutral (light + dark compatible)
